Sentencas: The cathode/electrolyte interface in anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with Ni-8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) anode, thin YSZ electrolyte and La0.8Sr0.2Mn1.1O3-delta (LSM)-YSZ composite cathode was modified by dispersed (CeO2)(0.01)-(SC2O3)(0.10)-(ZrO2)(0.89) (1Ce10ScZr) electrolyte.
Titulo: Anode-supported SOFC with 1Ce10ScZr modified cathode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: The two electrolytes were co-fired into a dense and continuous electrolyte film.
Titulo: Anode-supported SOFC with 1Ce10ScZr modified cathode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: By this method, the electrode polarization resistance, specifically the charge transfer resistance of oxygen ions, was greatly reduced.
Titulo: Anode-supported SOFC with 1Ce10ScZr modified cathode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: The modified cell achieved a higher performance than the unmodified one, especially at the lower operation temperatures.
Titulo: Anode-supported SOFC with 1Ce10ScZr modified cathode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: The decrease of electrode polarization resistance can be ascribed to the accelerated surface oxygen exchange rate from 1Ce10ScZr electrolyte at the cathode/electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Anode-supported SOFC with 1Ce10ScZr modified cathode/electrolyte interface
